# 📝 Note-Taking App

# A full-stack note-taking web app built with:

# - 🖥️ Frontend: React.js
# - ⚙️ Backend: Node.js + Express
# - 🗃️ Database: MongoDB (Atlas)
# - 🔐 Auth: JWT + OTP email verification (with Nodemailer)

## 🚀 Features

# - User signup with OTP email verification
# - JWT-based login & protected dashboard
# - Add, view, and delete personal notes
# - Responsive layout (mobile & desktop)
# - Logout and token handling
# - Deployed-ready structure

## 🔧 Project Structure

# note-taking-app/
# ├── client/ # React frontend
# ├── server/ # Express backend
# ├── .env # Environment variables
# └── README.md


## 📦 How to Run Locally

### 1. Clone the repository

# ```bash
# git clone https://github.com/yourusername/note-taking-app.git
# cd note-taking-app
# 2. Backend setup

# cd server
# npm install
# Add a .env file in the server folder with:

# env
# Copy
# Edit
# MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
# JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key
# EMAIL_USER=your_email@gmail.com
# EMAIL_PASS=your_16_char_app_password


# Then start the server:
# npm run dev



# 3. Frontend setup
# bash
# Copy
# Edit
# cd ../client
# npm install
# npm start